’s Frozen, for example, is explored in the context of the Soham murders (which took place while the play was in production at the National Theatre), whilst three virtually simultaneous productions of Euripides’ Hecuba are interpreted with regard to the Beslan massacre of schoolchildren.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aLiterature Studies 2020. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Theater / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aAn Inspector Calls.  aBeslan massacre.  aFar Away.  aFrozen.  aHecuba.  aSoham murders.  afictional time.  ahistorical moment.  alost children.  atheatre time.1 aCousin, Geraldine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978184779168940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847791689423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847791689/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles